{"id": "869193", "revid": "32911304", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=869193", "title": "Mine Ore", "text": "Mine Ore is a &lt;a href=\"Quests%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; available in . This is a &lt;a href=\"radiant%20quest\"&gt;radiant quest&lt;/a&gt; in which the &lt;a href=\"Last%20Dragonborn\"&gt;Dragonborn&lt;/a&gt; can earn for selling ore collected from ore veins in mines and the wild.\nWalkthrough.\nA citizen may give a suggestion of the radiant quest through dialogue, such as:\n\"Are you looking for work? The mines are nearby. You bring me ore, I'll give you coin.\"\nRegardless of whether prompted, approaching an ore vein with a &lt;a href=\"Pickaxe%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;pickaxe&lt;/a&gt; in your inventory and pressing the \"Activate\" button initiates mining. Ore or a gem will be awarded every few swings of the &lt;a href=\"Last%20Dragonborn\"&gt;Dragonborn&lt;/a&gt;'s mining animation until the vein is depleted or the player cancels the action. Mining can also be done in a faster, safer method by attacking an ore vein with a pickaxe, which will not require any animation to be canceled should the player need to. The ore can be sold to the quest giver, although they will only accept the type of ore found in the nearest mine. &lt;a href=\"Merchants%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;Merchants&lt;/a&gt; also accept ore for a lesser price along with the gems found in the veins."}
{"id": "558246", "revid": "32045548", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=558246", "title": "Mine Safety Regulations", "text": "Mine Safety Regulations is a &lt;a href=\"Books%20%28Online%29\"&gt;book&lt;/a&gt; in .\nContents.\nMine Safety Regulations\n\u2014 Shoring timbers should be at least a handspan in width and breadth.\n\u2014 Mine shafts should be shoread every three paces.\n\u2014 Mine shafts should not be wider than three paces nor higher than two paces.\n\u2014 Mine chambers should not be excavated wider than five paces between rock pillars left for roof support.\n\u2014 No shouting or other loud noises.\n\u2014 No running or horseplay.\n\u2014 No racing in the mining carts."}
