{"id": "117266", "revid": "30169600", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=117266", "title": "Miner Arobar's Support", "text": "Miner Arobar's Support is a &lt;a href=\"House%20Redoran\"&gt;House Redoran&lt;/a&gt; quest open to the &lt;a href=\"Nerevarine\"&gt;Nerevarine&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0during the events of .\nWalkthrough.\nOnce the Nerevarine has solved the issue of the &lt;a href=\"The%20Mad%20Lord%20of%20Milk\"&gt;Mad Lord of Milk&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Athyn%20Sarethi\"&gt;Athyn Sarethi&lt;/a&gt; will inform the Nerevarine that to advance further in &lt;a href=\"House%20Redoran\"&gt;House Redoran&lt;/a&gt;, they must obtain the support of the various councilors. He gives the Nerevarine the &lt;a href=\"Red%20Book%20of%203E%20426\"&gt;Red Book of 3E 426&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0and informs them about the other councilors. One such councilor goes by the name of &lt;a href=\"Miner%20Arobar\"&gt;Miner Arobar&lt;/a&gt; and can be won over to support the Nerevarine.\nArobar's Issues.\nThe Nerevarine must go to &lt;a href=\"Arobar%20Manor\"&gt;Arobar Manor&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Ald%27ruhn%2C%20Manor%20District\"&gt;Ald'ruhn, Manor District&lt;/a&gt; to find Arobar. The latter will, initially, refuse to even consider the Nerevarine for advancement in Redoran. Back in &lt;a href=\"Sarethi%20Manor\"&gt;Sarethi Manor&lt;/a&gt;, further discussion with &lt;a href=\"Athyn%20Sarethi\"&gt;Athyn Sarethi&lt;/a&gt; will reveal that Arobar may be influenced by &lt;a href=\"House%20Telvanni%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;House Telvanni&lt;/a&gt;. He, therefore, suggests that the Nerevarine travel to &lt;a href=\"Sadrith%20Mora%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;Sadrith Mora&lt;/a&gt; to investigate these influences.\nSadrith Mora.\nAsking around the town of Sadrith Mora will reveal that Arobar's niece, &lt;a href=\"Nartise%20Arobar\"&gt;Nartise Arobar&lt;/a&gt;, is being held prisoner in the local Telvanni tower of &lt;a href=\"Tel%20Naga%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;Tel Naga&lt;/a&gt;. Nartise can be found near the entrance of the tower, however she is guarded by three Telvanni guards (who will attack once Nartise is released). Having freed her from the tower, the Nerevarine must escort her to the Sadrith Mora dock.\nProblem solved.\nNow that Nartise is safe from House Telvanni, the Nerevarine may return to Arobar in Ald'ruhn, who will be grateful and agree to support the Nerevarine in the future.\u00a0"}
