{"id": "1060206", "revid": "32045548", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=1060206", "title": "Mining Misfortune", "text": "Mining Misfortune is a &lt;a href=\"Quests%20%28Blades%29\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; available in . It is centered around finding a group of lost miners. The recommened player level for this quest is level 22. Two secrets can be found during the quest.\nBackground.\n\"I need to look for some miners that have gone missing in a nearby cave.\"\"\nWalkthrough.\nIn the Town, the Hero is approached by &lt;a href=\"Varro%20Matius\"&gt;Varro Matius&lt;/a&gt;, who asks them for aid in finding a group of lost miners. Upon arriving at the camp, three villagers are found, providing the following quotes:\nTwo guards are also present, one on the western side of the camp and one on the northern side, providing the following quotes:\nFollowing the path, the Hero will encounter &lt;a href=\"Louis\"&gt;Louis&lt;/a&gt;, the head miner of the camp, who informs the Hero on the passageway. Entering the cave, the Hero finds numerous skeletons, and four dead miners. Progressing deeper into the cave, the Hero finds a Cave Troll on the left side of the cave, protecting a golden chest, and a small dock with ships. Along the docks, the Hero has to fight skeletons, while on one of the boats, the last miner is found. Speaking with the miner results in the following dialogue:\n\"They spoke to me...\"\nTalking to the miner again:\n\"Let me go!\"\nWith the key, the Hero must find the entrance to the hidden temple. After using the key, the Hero encounters two spiders, guarding the first secret of the quest. Following the other road, the Hero finds the temple entrance, where more spiders are found. Deeper inside the temple, a coffin is found, which is destroyed by the wight coming out of it, named Haeliaran, who fights with a dagger. Upon defeating the wight, the quest is completed. To the right of the coffin, the second secret is found."}
