{"id": "2364", "revid": "3200451", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2364", "title": "Bruma Mages Guild", "text": "Bruma Mages Guild is a &lt;a href=\"Mages%20Guild%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Mages Guild&lt;/a&gt; branch located in western &lt;a href=\"Bruma%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Bruma&lt;/a&gt; on the second tier in . It has trainers who train hopefuls in various types of magic. The Bruma chapterhouse has no definite &lt;a href=\"school%20of%20magic\"&gt;school of magic&lt;/a&gt;, instead having various. The Guild also sells various schools of &lt;a href=\"Spells%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;spells&lt;/a&gt;.\nHistory.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Hero%20of%20Kvatch\"&gt;Hero&lt;/a&gt; may come to the Guild to get his recommendation. He passed the recommendation quest with flying colors by finding the missing guild member &lt;a href=\"J%27skar\"&gt;J'skar&lt;/a&gt;, who it turns out was playing a trick on the Guild Hall Leader, &lt;a href=\"Jeanne%20Frasoric\"&gt;Jeanne Frasoric&lt;/a&gt; because she can't perform magic well but lords her position over the rest of the guild members at the Bruma chapterhouse of the Mages Guild.\nDuring the &lt;a href=\"Necromancy%20Purge\"&gt;Necromancy Purge&lt;/a&gt; the chapterhouse was stormed by &lt;a href=\"Mannimarco%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Mannimarco&lt;/a&gt;, his &lt;a href=\"Necromancer%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;necromancers&lt;/a&gt;, and his horde of &lt;a href=\"Undead%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt; soldiers. All of the guild members except J'skar died defending the guild. J'skar survived only because he turned himself invisible when all was lost."}
