{"id": "17173", "revid": "39973906", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=17173", "title": "Bruma Recommendation", "text": "Bruma Recommendation is a &lt;a href=\"Quests%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; in . As part of &lt;a href=\"Join%20the%20Mages%20Guild\"&gt;Join the Mages Guild&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Hero%20of%20Kvatch\"&gt;Hero&lt;/a&gt; must get a recommendation from each city's Mages Guild Hall.\nWalkthrough.\n&lt;a href=\"Jeanne%20Frasoric\"&gt;Jeanne Frasoric&lt;/a&gt; asks the Hero to try and find &lt;a href=\"J%27skar\"&gt;J'skar&lt;/a&gt;. He's been missing for some time and she cannot find him. Talk to &lt;a href=\"Volanaro%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Volanaro&lt;/a&gt; who says they must play a prank on Jeanne Frasoric first. Volanaro doesn't think that Jeanne is worthy of being their leader and often plays tricks on her.\nTalk to Volanaro and get the &lt;a href=\"disposition\"&gt;disposition&lt;/a&gt; high enough for him to offer to help them. He will teach them a spell to open easy locks, which costs less &lt;a href=\"Magicka%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;magicka&lt;/a&gt; than the normal &lt;a href=\"Open%20Easy%20Lock\"&gt;Open Easy Lock&lt;/a&gt; spell.\nThe prank involves going upstairs, unlocking Jeanne's desk using the scroll which Volanaro has taught them, or using a &lt;a href=\"Lockpick%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;lockpick&lt;/a&gt;.\u00a0It doesn't matter which way they open the desk. Then, they'll have to steal her &lt;a href=\"Manual%20of%20Spellcraft\"&gt;Manual of Spellcraft&lt;/a&gt;.\nVolanaro then tells them to wait until 10 pm and meet him downstairs in the living quarters. He will reveal J'skar to them, who never left the building but was simply invisible the whole time. The Hero can then go upstairs and wake up the Guild Leader and tell her they found him. After this Jeanne Frasoric will gladly send a recommendation to the &lt;a href=\"Arcane%20University%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Arcane University&lt;/a&gt;.\nAlternative walkthrough.\nAs a mage, they can easily find J'skar on their own with &lt;a href=\"Detect%20Life%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Detect Life&lt;/a&gt; and cast &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Dispel&lt;/a&gt; on him to make him visible again. If they are unable to dispel a target through distance or touch, the &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Other\"&gt;Dispel Other&lt;/a&gt; spell can be purchased from &lt;a href=\"Alves%20Uvenim\"&gt;Alves Uvenim&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Leyawiin%20Mages%20Guild\"&gt;Leyawiin Mages Guild&lt;/a&gt;. Do not &lt;a href=\"Stealing\"&gt;steal&lt;/a&gt; Jeanne's key, as this qualifies as a &lt;a href=\"Crime%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;crime&lt;/a&gt; against the guild, requiring immediate expulsion."}
