{"id": "38712", "revid": "44356307", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=38712", "title": "Bthuand (Morrowind)", "text": "Bthuand is a &lt;a href=\"Dwemer%20Ruins%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;Dwemer Ruin&lt;/a&gt; located in the the &lt;a href=\"Ashlands%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;Ashlands&lt;/a&gt; region in . It is southwest of &lt;a href=\"Rotheran\"&gt;Rotheran&lt;/a&gt; and northeast of &lt;a href=\"Falasmaryon\"&gt;Falasmaryon&lt;/a&gt;, just west of &lt;a href=\"Zergonipal%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;Zergonipal&lt;/a&gt;. Unusually for a Dwemer ruin, there are six dead scribs lying on the floors."}
{"id": "973089", "revid": "32045548", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=973089", "title": "Bthuand (Online)", "text": "Bthuand is a location that appears in , in the region of &lt;a href=\"Vvardenfell%20%28Online%29\"&gt;Vvardenfell&lt;/a&gt;. It is located west of &lt;a href=\"Zergonipal%20%28Online%29\"&gt;Zergonipal&lt;/a&gt; and southeast of the &lt;a href=\"Forgotten%20Wastes\"&gt;Forgotten Wastes&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "127520", "revid": "17401442", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=127520", "title": "Bthuand Mzahnch", "text": "Bthuand Mzahnch was one of the &lt;a href=\"Tonal%20Architect\"&gt;Tonal Architect&lt;/a&gt;s, and is the &lt;a href=\"author\"&gt;author&lt;/a&gt; of \"&lt;a href=\"The%20Egg%20of%20Time\"&gt;The Egg of Time&lt;/a&gt;\". In it, Bthuand argues against the idea that tapping the power of &lt;a href=\"Lorkhan%27s%20Heart\"&gt;Lorkhan's Heart&lt;/a&gt; is too dangerous. Some believed that using the Heart would have side effects, but the Tonal Architects argued that no unforeseen consequences could result from their work."}
{"id": "278594", "revid": "43547943", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=278594", "title": "Bthuangth's Harvester", "text": "Bthuangth's Harvester is a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Items%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;unique&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Handedness%20%28Morrowind%29%23Two-hand\"&gt;Two-Handed&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Dwarven%20Weapons%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;Dwarven&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;weapon&lt;/a&gt;. It is enchanted to cast &lt;a href=\"Soul%20Trap%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;soultrap&lt;/a&gt; on strike, simplifying the capture of an opponent's &lt;a href=\"soul\"&gt;soul&lt;/a&gt; in a &lt;a href=\"Soul%20Gem%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;gem&lt;/a&gt; for use in &lt;a href=\"Enchant%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;enchanting&lt;/a&gt;.\nAcquisition.\nThis &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Morrowind%29%23Spear\"&gt;halberd&lt;/a&gt; can be found at &lt;a href=\"Dandera%20Selaro\"&gt;Dandera Selaro's&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Ald%27ruhn%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;Ald'ruhn&lt;/a&gt;. She is outside, selling her wares at the stall near the front door. &lt;a href=\"Sneak%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;Stealth&lt;/a&gt; must be used to unlock the door (requiring 50 &lt;a href=\"Security%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;Security&lt;/a&gt;) and enter without being detected. Once inside, there is nobody present and it can be stolen without fear of being caught. Only a portion of it is in plain sight, it is mostly hidden behind the bed and locked closet."}
{"id": "38713", "revid": "44356307", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=38713", "title": "Bthungthumz", "text": "Bthungthumz is a &lt;a href=\"Dwemer%20Ruins%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;Dwemer ruin&lt;/a&gt; located in the &lt;a href=\"Ashlands%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;Ashlands&lt;/a&gt; in . It is southeast of &lt;a href=\"Khuul\"&gt;Khuul&lt;/a&gt; and northeast of &lt;a href=\"Maar%20Gan\"&gt;Maar Gan&lt;/a&gt;. The entrance to the ruin is hidden beneath a bridge and behind some rocks (see &lt;a href=\"%23Gallery\"&gt;gallery&lt;/a&gt; image below)."}
