{"id": "1512", "revid": "32045548", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=1512", "title": "Buoyant Armigers (Morrowind)", "text": "The Buoyant Armigers are a group of guards serving the god &lt;a href=\"Vivec\"&gt;Vivec&lt;/a&gt;. Their base of operation is the &lt;a href=\"Ghostgate\"&gt;Ghostgate&lt;/a&gt; and seem to, also, follow and serve &lt;a href=\"Imperial%20Law\"&gt;Imperial Law&lt;/a&gt; in this setting. They protect the &lt;a href=\"Tribunal%20Temple\"&gt;temple&lt;/a&gt; pilgrims as well as warriors that help keep the &lt;a href=\"blight\"&gt;blight&lt;/a&gt;ed creatures from invading &lt;a href=\"Vvardenfell%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;Vvardenfell&lt;/a&gt;. They commonly wear &lt;a href=\"Chitin%20Armor%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;Chitin Armor&lt;/a&gt;, and higher-ranked members may wear &lt;a href=\"Glass%20Armor%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;Glass&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Daedric%20Armor%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;Daedric Armor&lt;/a&gt;.\nBackground.\nThe Buoyant Armigers reportedly came into being after &lt;a href=\"Vivec\"&gt;Vivec&lt;/a&gt; heard of three lesser houses spreading \"doubtful doctrine\" from a place known as &lt;a href=\"Red%20Mountain\"&gt;Horde Mountain&lt;/a&gt;, a mountain made of many warriors. In response, he cast the creatures that made up Horde Mountain's bones to the heavens so that they made &lt;a href=\"Vivec%20City%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;Vivec City&lt;/a&gt;. The ones who cheered at Vivec's coming, the &lt;a href=\"Veloth\"&gt;Veloth&lt;/a&gt;i, became the Buoyant Armigers, and the three houses were married under Vivec's merriment to form one great one.\nThe Buoyant Armigers Grand Marshall is &lt;a href=\"Galdal%20Omayn\"&gt;Galdal Omayn&lt;/a&gt;, and all Armigers as well as most militaristic factions of the &lt;a href=\"Tribunal%20Temple\"&gt;Tribunal Temple&lt;/a&gt; seem to at least respect, if not function, as members of &lt;a href=\"House%20Redoran\"&gt;House Redoran&lt;/a&gt;."}
