{"id": "201326", "revid": "44356307", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=201326", "title": "Burden (Morrowind)", "text": "Burden is a magic effect and a &lt;a href=\"Spells%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;spell&lt;/a&gt; in that is a member of the &lt;a href=\"Alteration%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;Alteration&lt;/a&gt; school of magic, governed by &lt;a href=\"Willpower%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;Willpower&lt;/a&gt;. Its base &lt;a href=\"Magicka%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;Magicka&lt;/a&gt; cost is 1.00 point.\nCharacters.\nThe following &lt;a href=\"Characters%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;people&lt;/a&gt; use this spell:\nSpells.\nThe following spells consist of a Burden effect. They may include additional effects. See articles for details.\nMerchants.\nThe following &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Merchants%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;spell merchants&lt;/a&gt; are purveyors of one or more spells consisting of a Burden effect:\nItems.\nThe following items consist of a Burden effect. They may include additional effects. See articles for details.\nWeapons.\nWeapon damage varies by attack type (chop, slash, or thrust). Refer to individual articles for detailed information."}
{"id": "17292", "revid": "32911304", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=17292", "title": "Burden (Oblivion)", "text": "Burden is an &lt;a href=\"Alteration%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Alteration&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Spells%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;spell&lt;/a&gt; that temporarily adds &lt;a href=\"Encumbrance%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;weight&lt;/a&gt; to the target's &lt;a href=\"inventory\"&gt;inventory&lt;/a&gt;, sometimes immobilizing them. It seems to have no effects on animals, but humanoid &lt;a href=\"daedra\"&gt;daedra&lt;/a&gt; are still affected.\nAcquisition.\nBurden can be obtained at lower &lt;a href=\"level\"&gt;level&lt;/a&gt;s, and always available at &lt;a href=\"Edgar%27s%20Discount%20Spells\"&gt;Edgar's Discount Spells&lt;/a&gt;. Members of the &lt;a href=\"Cheydinhal%20Mages%20Guild\"&gt;Cheydinhal Mages Guild&lt;/a&gt; sell Alteration spells, including leveled Burden spells. &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Merchants%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Spell Merchants&lt;/a&gt; at the &lt;a href=\"Arcane%20University%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Arcane University&lt;/a&gt; may have access to this spell effect. Once purchased, &lt;a href=\"Spellmaking%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;custom spells&lt;/a&gt; containing the Burden effect can be created at an &lt;a href=\"Altar%20of%20Spellmaking%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Altar of Spellmaking&lt;/a&gt;.\nInteractions.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Cheydinhal%20Recommendation\"&gt;Cheydinhal Recommendation&lt;/a&gt; offers a tutorial of &lt;a href=\"Feather%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Feather&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Water%20Breathing%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Water Breathing&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Burden%20%28Effect%29\"&gt;Burden&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"Vidkun\"&gt;Vidkun&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Cheydinhal%20Mages%20Guild\"&gt;guildhall's&lt;/a&gt; previous &lt;a href=\"associate\"&gt;associate&lt;/a&gt;, drowned because he wore a &lt;a href=\"Ring%20of%20Burden\"&gt;Ring of Burden&lt;/a&gt; underwater. First appearing in , the spell was discontinued in\u00a0, along with Feather and &lt;a href=\"Open%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Open&lt;/a&gt;.\nUsefulness.\nTo maximize effectiveness, it should be paired with &lt;a href=\"Drain%20Strength\"&gt;Drain Strength&lt;/a&gt;, which lowers the weight limit on characters. Though not the most useful spell, many enemies utilize it to help bring you down. Its true usefulness shines when used in poisons, along with a Burden and Drain Strength enchantment on whatever weapon you are using.\nIt is possible create a custom spell at an Altar of Spellmaking, which casts Burden on self. This can be used underwater to kill oneself."}
