{"id": "612345", "revid": "32045548", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=612345", "title": "Valley of Blades", "text": "Valley of Blades is a &lt;a href=\"Quests%20%28Online%29\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; available in . The group heads to the &lt;a href=\"Valley%20of%20the%20Blades\"&gt;Valley of the Blades&lt;/a&gt; to find &lt;a href=\"Kasura\"&gt;Kasura&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Sai%20Sahan%20%28Online%29\"&gt;Sai Sahan&lt;/a&gt;'s friend whom he entrusted with a ring to keep the &lt;a href=\"Amulet%20of%20Kings%20%28Online%29\"&gt;Amulet of Kings&lt;/a&gt; safe. However, the Valley is burning when the &lt;a href=\"Vestige\"&gt;Vestige&lt;/a&gt; and their friends arrive.\nBackground.\n\"Varen has asked me to accompany Sai Sahan on a trip back to his ancestral home. An old friend, Kasura, may have knowledge of how to sneak into Sancre Tor.\"\nSummary.\n&lt;a href=\"The%20Harborage%20%28Location%29\"&gt;The Harborage&lt;/a&gt; is the same for all &lt;a href=\"alliances\"&gt;alliances&lt;/a&gt;. However, the closest city will change based on the chosen faction.\nWalkthrough.\nThe group heads to the Valley of the Blades to find Kasura, Sai Sahan's friend whom he entrusted with a ring to keep the &lt;a href=\"Amulet%20of%20Kings%20%28Online%29\"&gt;Amulet of Kings&lt;/a&gt; safe. However, the Valley is burning when the Vestige and their friends arrive.\nAfter talking to Kasura, three &lt;a href=\"Sigil%20Stone%20%28Online%29\"&gt;sigil stones&lt;/a&gt; must be destroyed to close the portals to &lt;a href=\"Oblivion%20%28Realm%29\"&gt;Oblivion&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"Order%20of%20the%20Black%20Worm%20%28Online%29\"&gt;Worm Cultists&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Daedra%20%28Online%29\"&gt;Daedra&lt;/a&gt; will appear by each stone. &lt;a href=\"Mannimarco%20%28Online%29\"&gt;Mannimarco&lt;/a&gt; then summons a Daedric Titan to attack the party.\nKasura reveals that she kept the &lt;a href=\"Ring%20of%20Stendarr%27s%20Mercy\"&gt;Ring of Stendarr's Mercy&lt;/a&gt; in an ancient crypt. The Vestige must take the ring quickly, now that Mannimarco knows where they are. Almost as soon as one takes the ring from its hiding place, Mannimarco appears. He summons &lt;a href=\"Undead%20%28Online%29\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Ansei\"&gt;Ansei&lt;/a&gt; to attack the group. &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Bolts\"&gt;Silver Bolts&lt;/a&gt; is very useful here to both knock them down and draw out a single enemy at a time, making the fights much easier.\n&lt;a href=\"Lyris%20Titanborn%20%28Online%29\"&gt;Lyris&lt;/a&gt;, Sahan and &lt;a href=\"Abnur%20Tharn%20%28Online%29\"&gt;Tharn&lt;/a&gt; decide to stay behind with Kasura to help her bury her students and rebuild. The Vestige reports to &lt;a href=\"Varen%20Aquilarios%20%28Online%29\"&gt;Varen&lt;/a&gt; what they found."}
