{"id": "1050286", "revid": "24405068", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=1050286", "title": "Vamidium", "text": "Vamidium are &lt;a href=\"Dwemer\"&gt;Dwemer&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"animunculi\"&gt;animunculi&lt;/a&gt;, ancient mechanical automatons, designed to look and function as beasts of burden. Imitating nature with mechanical constructs, they were most often used as mounts and found amongst &lt;a href=\"Dwemer%20ruins\"&gt;Dwemer ruins&lt;/a&gt; stretching from &lt;a href=\"Hammerfell\"&gt;Hammerfell&lt;/a&gt; to &lt;a href=\"Morrowind\"&gt;Morrowind&lt;/a&gt;. Like other animunculi, vamidiums appear to utilize &lt;a href=\"soul%20gem\"&gt;soul gem&lt;/a&gt;s, steam or &lt;a href=\"dynamo%20core\"&gt;dynamo core&lt;/a&gt;s as their power source. The existence of ancient Dwarven horse armor evidences that the Dwemer did not exclusively rely upon these mechanical creatures, however. The most common type are the &lt;a href=\"Dwarven%20spider\"&gt;Dwarven spider&lt;/a&gt;.\nMany vamidiums were collected by the &lt;a href=\"Mages%20Guild\"&gt;Mages Guild&lt;/a&gt; and stored in the vaults below the &lt;a href=\"Arcane%20University\"&gt;Arcane University&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Second%20Era\"&gt;Second Era&lt;/a&gt;. When the forces of &lt;a href=\"Molag%20Bal\"&gt;Molag Bal&lt;/a&gt; overran the &lt;a href=\"Imperial%20City\"&gt;Imperial City&lt;/a&gt; during the &lt;a href=\"Planemeld\"&gt;Planemeld&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"2E%20582\"&gt;2E 582&lt;/a&gt;, many of these rare artifacts were smuggled out of the city and began to appear on the open market all over Tamriel.\nTrivia.\nVamidiums should not be confused with &lt;a href=\"fabricants\"&gt;fabricants&lt;/a&gt;, which are partially organic mechanical constructs created by &lt;a href=\"Sotha%20Sil\"&gt;Sotha Sil&lt;/a&gt;, also known to be used as mounts."}
