{"id": "746923", "revid": "17401442", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=746923", "title": "Vampire's Seduction (Oblivion)", "text": "Vampire's Seduction is a &lt;a href=\"greater%20power\"&gt;greater power&lt;/a&gt; acquired by &lt;a href=\"Vampire%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;vampires&lt;/a&gt; in upon reaching stage two of &lt;a href=\"Vampirism%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;vampirism&lt;/a&gt;. This skill can be used to bypass the huge &lt;a href=\"disposition\"&gt;disposition&lt;/a&gt; penalty that comes with being a high level vampire.\nBeing a greater power, vampire's seduction can only be used once per day."}
{"id": "142906", "revid": "25356303", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=142906", "title": "Vampire's Seduction (Skyrim)", "text": "Vampire's Seduction is a stage-two &lt;a href=\"Vampirism%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;vampire power&lt;/a&gt; in \u00a0that reduces the target's inclination to attack for 30 seconds. The magnitude is level affected \u2013 the power only works on characters/creatures up to the level specified. &lt;a href=\"Undead%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;Undead&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Daedra\"&gt;Daedra&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"automatons\"&gt;automatons&lt;/a&gt; cannot be seduced, unless the player has the &lt;a href=\"Master%20of%20the%20Mind\"&gt;Master of the Mind&lt;/a&gt; perk. The &lt;a href=\"Level%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;level&lt;/a&gt; may be increased to 20 if the \"&lt;a href=\"Hypnotic%20Gaze\"&gt;Hypnotic Gaze&lt;/a&gt;\" and \"&lt;a href=\"Kindred%20Mage\"&gt;Kindred Mage&lt;/a&gt;\" &lt;a href=\"Perks%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;perks&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Illusion%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;Illusion&lt;/a&gt; are unlocked. It can only be used once a day.\nWith the &lt;a href=\"Official%20Plug-ins%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;DLC&lt;/a&gt;, this power allows conscious people to be fed upon.\nAcquisition.\nVampire's Seduction can only be acquired when the Dragonborn enters stage two &lt;a href=\"Vampirism%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;Vampirism&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "122482", "revid": "30169600", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=122482", "title": "Vampire's Servant", "text": "Vampire's Servant is one of the &lt;a href=\"Powers%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;powers&lt;/a&gt; the &lt;a href=\"Last%20Dragonborn\"&gt;Dragonborn&lt;/a&gt; receives as they progress as a &lt;a href=\"Vampirism%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;Vampire&lt;/a&gt;. It allows the reanimation of a very powerful body to fight alongside for 60 seconds. As a power it can only be used once per day.\nUnlike necromancy spells of the &lt;a href=\"Conjuration%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;Conjuration&lt;/a&gt; spell tree, the victims of Vampire's Servant does not turn to ash when the effect wears off after 60 seconds (except during the first stage of vampirism). It is similar to &lt;a href=\"Dead%20Thrall\"&gt;Dead Thrall&lt;/a&gt; of the conjuration tree, but it can be used on any dead corpse. Therefore, it is not a true thrall: At the moment of casting it is more powerful (as the Dragonborn can raise whatever creature they want), but much less effective for long fights.\nApparently, the perk &lt;a href=\"Necromage%20%28Perk%29\"&gt;Necromage&lt;/a&gt; does not influence the duration of this Power, unlike the spells of the Conjuration tree."}
{"id": "147446", "revid": "29041419", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=147446", "title": "Vampire's Sight", "text": "Vampire's Sight is a lesser &lt;a href=\"Powers%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;power&lt;/a&gt; learned by &lt;a href=\"Vampire%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;vampires&lt;/a&gt; upon reaching stage one of &lt;a href=\"Vampirism%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;vampirism&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe effect grants &lt;a href=\"Night%20Eye%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;Night Vision&lt;/a&gt; for 60 seconds. Like the &lt;a href=\"Khajiit%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;Khajiit&lt;/a&gt; racial ability &lt;a href=\"Night%20Eye%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;Night Eye&lt;/a&gt;, it can be toggled on and off and can be used an unlimited number of times per day.\nAdditionally, it can be used when transformed into a &lt;a href=\"Vampire%20Lord\"&gt;Vampire Lord&lt;/a&gt; (see &lt;a href=\"Vampire%20Sight\"&gt;Vampire Sight&lt;/a&gt;)."}
{"id": "71646", "revid": "26213507", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=71646", "title": "Vampire's Thrall", "text": " \nVampire's Thralls are &lt;a href=\"Creatures%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;creatures&lt;/a&gt; that are the result of the \u00a0&lt;a href=\"Vampire%27s%20Servant\"&gt;Vampire's Servant&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0in .\nCharacteristics.\nVampire thralls are beings that are forcibly under the control of a &lt;a href=\"Vampire%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;vampire&lt;/a&gt;, and thus possess no free will of their own. They will attack any person or creature, which isn't of the same kind or a vampire, including the &lt;a href=\"Last%20Dragonborn\"&gt;Dragonborn&lt;/a&gt; on sight.\nInteractions.\nBe wary, as finding a thrall guarantees that a vampire will be nearby. Based on their armor and their ability to wield weapons and occasionally magic, it can be theorized that they are former bandits or adventurers. Even though the thralls seem to have no free will, they appear to have retained some measure of greed. For instance, in the quest \"&lt;a href=\"Laid%20to%20Rest\"&gt;Laid to Rest&lt;/a&gt;,\" the Dragonborn may see and hear a vampire thrall searching bodies.\nIn the expansion, if the Dragonborn decides to become a Vampire Lord, more insight is revealed into how thralls can be made. Although vampire's thralls may not be created by the Dragonborn during normal gameplay, in \"&lt;a href=\"Prophet%20%28Vampire%29\"&gt;Prophet&lt;/a&gt;,\" a thrall is used by the Dragonborn to pursue Harkon's goals. They are tasked with creating a thrall from a &lt;a href=\"Moth%20Priest\"&gt;Moth Priest&lt;/a&gt; and forcing him to read an &lt;a href=\"Elder%20Scrolls\"&gt;Elder Scroll&lt;/a&gt;; as such, &lt;a href=\"Dexion%20Evicus\"&gt;Dexion Evicus&lt;/a&gt; is forced into enthrallment by the Dragonborn.\nYou may not create thralls besides the one you make for the storyline."}
