{"id": "71640", "revid": "17401442", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=71640", "title": "Vampire Mistwalker", "text": "Vampire Mistwalker is a type of &lt;a href=\"Vampire%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;vampire&lt;/a&gt; in that is &lt;a href=\"Random%20Encounters%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;encountered randomly&lt;/a&gt; throughout &lt;a href=\"Skyrim\"&gt;Skyrim&lt;/a&gt;. Their &lt;a href=\"Races%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;race&lt;/a&gt; is radiant. Their &lt;a href=\"Vampiric%20Drain%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;Vampiric Drain&lt;/a&gt; absorbs both &lt;a href=\"Health%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;health&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Stamina%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;stamina&lt;/a&gt; from their targets, making them much more dangerous than their Fledgling and Blooded counterparts\nInteractions.\n&lt;a href=\"Hitting%20the%20Books\"&gt;Hitting the Books&lt;/a&gt;.\nVampire Mistwalkers can be found imprisoned in &lt;a href=\"Fellglow%20Keep\"&gt;Fellglow Keep&lt;/a&gt;. After picking their locks they will move towards the closest exit and fight anything, except the Dragonborn's party, on their way out until stopping close to the exit. If spoken to, they will say \"Out of the way, meat.\" \nDialogue.\nIf a powerful enough &lt;a href=\"Calm%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;calming&lt;/a&gt; spell, or &lt;a href=\"Voice%20of%20the%20Emperor%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;Voice of the Emperor&lt;/a&gt;, is used during combat against a Vampire Mistwalker, she will have a &lt;a href=\"Generic%20Dialogue%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;generic&lt;/a&gt; greeting dialogue. If Dawnguard is installed, some will instead say \"Don't speak to me, meat\""}
{"id": "120250", "revid": "32045548", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=120250", "title": "Vampire Monk", "text": "Vampire Monk is an &lt;a href=\"Imperials%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Imperial&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Vampire%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;vampire&lt;/a&gt;. There are three variants; two females and one male.\nThey wear vampire clothing along with both leveled &lt;a href=\"Light%20Armor%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;light armor&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Heavy%20Armor%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;heavy armor&lt;/a&gt; and carry a few &lt;a href=\"Lockpick%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;lockpicks&lt;/a&gt;. Vampires can usually be found in &lt;a href=\"Caves%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;caves&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Forts%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;forts&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Ayleid%20Ruins%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Ayleid ruins&lt;/a&gt;."}
