{"id": "26727", "revid": "5064773", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=26727", "title": "Vampirism Cure Potion", "text": "Vampirism Cure Potion, also known as the Cure for Vampirism, is a &lt;a href=\"Potions%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;potion&lt;/a&gt; in , made from &lt;a href=\"Garlic%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Garlic&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Bloodgrass\"&gt;Bloodgrass&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Nightshade%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Nightshade&lt;/a&gt;, and the blood of an &lt;a href=\"Argonians%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Argonian&lt;/a&gt;. Two samples are given by &lt;a href=\"Melisande\"&gt;Melisande&lt;/a&gt;, the witch of &lt;a href=\"Drakelowe\"&gt;Drakelowe&lt;/a&gt;, during \"&lt;a href=\"Vampire%20Cure%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Vampire Cure&lt;/a&gt;.\" One is intended for consumption, while the other is reserved for &lt;a href=\"Rona%20Hassildor\"&gt;Rona Hassildor&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Count\"&gt;Count&lt;/a&gt;ess of &lt;a href=\"Skingrad%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Skingrad&lt;/a&gt;.\nProperties.\nAs a &lt;a href=\"Quest%20Items%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;quest item&lt;/a&gt;, it cannot be dropped, sold, or destroyed without use of console commands. Drinking it permanently cures &lt;a href=\"Vampirism%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;vampirism&lt;/a&gt; and restores &lt;a href=\"Health%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Health&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Magicka%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Magicka&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Fatigue%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Fatigue&lt;/a&gt; by 500 points. After it has been drunk, vampirism cannot be acquired again without &lt;a href=\"Console%20Commands%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;console commands&lt;/a&gt;, although &lt;a href=\"Porphyric%20Hemophilia%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Porphyric Hemophilia&lt;/a&gt; can."}
