{"id": "17051", "revid": "3245833", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=17051", "title": "Steel Weapons (Oblivion)", "text": "Steel Weapons are one of the most common types of &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;weaponry&lt;/a&gt; found in &lt;a href=\"Cyrodiil\"&gt;Cyrodiil&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nSteel weapons are more durable and stronger than &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Weapons%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;iron weapons&lt;/a&gt;. They begin appearing &lt;a href=\"Random%20Loot%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;randomly&lt;/a&gt; in the world and on opponents after &lt;a href=\"level\"&gt;level&lt;/a&gt; 2.\nWeapons.\nIn addition to the standard \"Steel weapons,\" there are \"Fine Steel\" weapons. They are generally lighter, worth more, and do slightly more damage, but are rarer in the game world.\nOther steel weapons.\nSteel Cutlass.\nA &lt;a href=\"Steel%20Cutlass\"&gt;Steel Cutlass&lt;/a&gt; technically falls under the &lt;a href=\"Longswords%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;longsword&lt;/a&gt; category. It is very rare; the easiest way to acquire one (or several) is through mission \"&lt;a href=\"The%20Ghost%20Ship%20of%20Anvil\"&gt;The Ghost Ship of Anvil&lt;/a&gt;.\" Another method is going to the &lt;a href=\"Imperial%20City%20Waterfront\"&gt;Imperial City Waterfront&lt;/a&gt;, which holds a ship inhabited by non-hostile pirates armed with cutlasses."}
{"id": "54082", "revid": "32045548", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=54082", "title": "Steel Weapons (Skyrim)", "text": "Steel Weapons are among the more common &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;weapons&lt;/a&gt; found on mid-range &lt;a href=\"Creatures%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;enemies&lt;/a&gt;. Steel weapons rank above &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Weapons%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;iron weapons&lt;/a&gt; and below &lt;a href=\"Elven%20Weapons%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;elven weapons&lt;/a&gt;. The steel weapon family contains &lt;a href=\"Axe%20%28Weapon%29\"&gt;axes&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Warhammers%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;warhammers&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Swords%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;swords&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Daggers%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;daggers&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Maces%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;maces&lt;/a&gt;. Unlike other weapon sets, there is no steel &lt;a href=\"Bows%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;bow&lt;/a&gt;; however, &lt;a href=\"Steel%20Arrow%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;steel arrows&lt;/a&gt; exist. An upgraded form of steel called \"&lt;a href=\"Skyforge%20Steel\"&gt;Skyforge Steel&lt;/a&gt;\" can be bought from &lt;a href=\"Eorlund%20Gray-Mane\"&gt;Eorlund Gray-Mane&lt;/a&gt; once the &lt;a href=\"The%20Companions\"&gt;The Companions&lt;/a&gt; have been joined. All steel weapons in are engraved with &lt;a href=\"Nords%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;Nordic&lt;/a&gt; art patterns and runes, particularly around the hilt.\u00a0\nAttributes by piece.\n - required\n\u2020 Crafting Steel Arrows requires to be installed. Each recipe yields 24 arrows."}
