{"id": "981573", "revid": "32045548", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=981573", "title": "Steelheart Vanquisher", "text": "Steelheart Vanquisher is a &lt;a href=\"Creatures%20%28Legends%29\"&gt;creature&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"card\"&gt;card&lt;/a&gt; in that is a part of the expansion.\nStrategy.\nSteelheart Vanquisher is an Orc card that is mostly of use only to other Orc decks. Steelheart Vanquisher is very effective at buffing friendly Orcs, but it can be tricky to use, as the card has limited health and power. It is best played in the Shadow Lane, and should be protected by guards if possible. It is also best to play this card when other Orc cards are already in play. Because of the card's limited power and health, Steelheart Vanquisher is a good target for equipment, healing and other buffs."}
{"id": "59828", "revid": "29041419", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=59828", "title": "Steepfall Burrow", "text": "Steepfall Burrow is a &lt;a href=\"Caves%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;cave&lt;/a&gt; located in .\nLocation.\nIt is a location in the &lt;a href=\"Haafingar\"&gt;Haafingar&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Holds\"&gt;Hold&lt;/a&gt;. It lies high in the northern peaks in Haafingar's central mountains. Steepfall Burrow also features a lower exit, which is a separate location on the map. This connection is often used by travelers to facilitate their trek through Haafingar's treacherous mountains.\nWalkthrough.\nThere are two different entrances to this cave, an upper and lower one. The upper level contains the quest related \"Noster's Helmet.\" As one enters the upper cave, follow the path around the corner to a room with a bridge over a large chasm. A &lt;a href=\"Frost%20Troll%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;frost troll&lt;/a&gt; will be waiting on the other side. Enter the ice cave behind this troll to encounter a second frost troll. (To avoid combat with these, one may use &lt;a href=\"Unrelenting%20Force%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;Unrelenting Force&lt;/a&gt; to throw them into the chasm, although if you plan to go into the water for the chest, the trolls may still be alive and may still be able to attack in the water.) The path will turn left. A skeleton can be found on the ground with some loot, including a skill book.\nAt the end of this path is a chest as well as a coin purse. The chest will contain Noster's Helmet (if he requested that it be retrieved) as well as other leveled loot. If going through the quest \"&lt;a href=\"Totems%20of%20Hircine\"&gt;Totems of Hircine&lt;/a&gt;,\" the totem will be located in this chest."}
