{"id": "2002", "revid": "17401442", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2002", "title": "Stendarr", "text": "Stendarr, also known as S'rendarr, is the &lt;a href=\"God\"&gt;God&lt;/a&gt; of Righteous Might and Merciful Forbearance. He is the inspiration of magistrates and rulers, the patron of the &lt;a href=\"Imperial%20Legion\"&gt;Imperial Legion&lt;/a&gt;s and the comfort of the law-abiding citizen. Stendarr has evolved from his &lt;a href=\"Nord\"&gt;Nord&lt;/a&gt;ic origins into a deity of compassion or sometimes, righteous rule. He is said to have accompanied &lt;a href=\"Tiber%20Septim\"&gt;Tiber Septim&lt;/a&gt; in his later years. In early &lt;a href=\"Altmer\"&gt;Altmer&lt;/a&gt;i legends, Stendarr is the apologist of Men.\nChapels.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Chapel%20of%20Stendarr\"&gt;Chapel of Stendarr&lt;/a&gt; is located in &lt;a href=\"Chorrol\"&gt;Chorrol&lt;/a&gt;, and, according to legend, the &lt;a href=\"Gauntlets%20of%20the%20Divine%20Crusader\"&gt;Gauntlets of the Divine Crusader&lt;/a&gt; are located there.\nCults and followers.\n&lt;a href=\"Vigilants%20of%20Stendarr\"&gt;Vigilants of Stendarr&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Skyrim\"&gt;Skyrim&lt;/a&gt;, the fanatical Vigilants of Stendarr wander the countryside, looking to distribute justice. On being questioned, Vigilants say that they formed their order after the &lt;a href=\"Oblivion%20Crisis\"&gt;Oblivion Crisis&lt;/a&gt;. Their objective is to eradicate certain undesirables from &lt;a href=\"Nirn\"&gt;Nirn&lt;/a&gt;, namely &lt;a href=\"Necromancer%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;necromancers&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Conjurer%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;conjurers&lt;/a&gt;, and especially &lt;a href=\"Daedra\"&gt;Daedra&lt;/a&gt;. They are also involved in trying to expunge Daedric worshippers from houses. When the &lt;a href=\"Volkihar%20Vampire\"&gt;Volkihar Vampire&lt;/a&gt;s attacked, the Vigilants lost their main base of operations within Skyrim, known as the &lt;a href=\"Hall%20of%20the%20Vigilant\"&gt;Hall of the Vigilant&lt;/a&gt;, as well as the head of their Order, &lt;a href=\"Keeper%20Carcette\"&gt;Keeper Carcette&lt;/a&gt;. The Vigilants as a whole were under attack by the vampires, with only their bastion at &lt;a href=\"Stendarr%27s%20Beacon\"&gt;Stendarr's Beacon&lt;/a&gt; near the &lt;a href=\"Morrowind\"&gt;Morrowind&lt;/a&gt; border remaining as a safe location within Skyrim. It is unknown how many Vigilants of Stendarr remained after the attack, due to most Vigilants living as nomads and the ones with the knowledge of their numbers having been killed. Still, the Vigilants did engage with the vampires in the wilderness, though on occassion the vampires beat them and took on their garments in attempts to lure unsuspecting travelers.\n&lt;a href=\"Crusaders\"&gt;Crusaders&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe knightly Order dedicated to the Temple of Stendarr, the Crusaders are tasked with protecting His Temples and acting as his blade when the situation demands it. Much like the other knightly orders of the Divines, the Crusaders are involved in a variety of tasks. These include exorcisms of both homes and children, purging heretics aiming to weaken the faith, finding missing scholars, pacifying mad priests, delivering of items, finding holy relics, destroying cursed items of evil, cleansing locations plagued by undead, and safeguarding relics. In times where Stendarr is mad with the Temple, the Crusaders also perform rites of atonement. The Crusaders are also involved in healing the sick.\nArtifacts.\n&lt;a href=\"Gauntlets%20of%20the%20Crusader\"&gt;Gauntlets of the Crusader&lt;/a&gt;.\nStendarr gifted the Gauntlets of the Crusader to &lt;a href=\"Pelinal%20Whitestrake\"&gt;Pelinal Whitestrake&lt;/a&gt;. They were deemed lost for some time, but were eventually recovered by the &lt;a href=\"Knights%20of%20the%20Nine%20%28Faction%29\"&gt;Knights of the Nine&lt;/a&gt;. They were subsequently used by &lt;a href=\"Sir%20Casimir\"&gt;Sir Casimir&lt;/a&gt; when he fought in the &lt;a href=\"War%20of%20the%20Red%20Diamond\"&gt;War of the Red Diamond&lt;/a&gt;. Some time after Sir Casimir returned from war, he struck down a beggar in the Chapel of Stendarr in Chorrol, and the gauntlets slipped from his hands and lay immovable on the floor. They would eventually be picked up by the &lt;a href=\"Hero%20of%20Kvatch\"&gt;Hero of Kvatch&lt;/a&gt; after the hero displayed mercy by taking the curse put on Casimir's heir onto themselves.\n&lt;a href=\"Stendarr%27s%20Hammer\"&gt;Stendarr's Hammer&lt;/a&gt;.\nAccording to rumor, Stendarr was said to have wielded his eponymous hammer himself, and the weight of it was so immense as to require four men to lift. In &lt;a href=\"3E%20427\"&gt;3E 427&lt;/a&gt;, the hammer was displayed under guard at &lt;a href=\"Mournhold\"&gt;Mournhold&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"Museum%20of%20Artifacts\"&gt;Museum of Artifacts&lt;/a&gt; in Morrowind, having been acquired through unknown means by the museum's curator, &lt;a href=\"Torasa%20Aram\"&gt;Torasa Aram&lt;/a&gt;. By &lt;a href=\"4E%20180\"&gt;4E 180&lt;/a&gt;, the hammer was the in the possession of the &lt;a href=\"Fugitive%20%28Blades%29\"&gt;Fugitive&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Cyrodiil\"&gt;Cyrodiil&lt;/a&gt;. In &lt;a href=\"4E%20201\"&gt;4E 201&lt;/a&gt;, the hammer was displayed in &lt;a href=\"Markarth\"&gt;Markarth&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"Dwemer%20Museum\"&gt;Dwemer Museum&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Skyrim\"&gt;Skyrim&lt;/a&gt; under the curatorship of &lt;a href=\"Calcelmo\"&gt;Calcelmo&lt;/a&gt; after having been found deep under the city. It was then taken by the &lt;a href=\"Last%20Dragonborn\"&gt;Last Dragonborn&lt;/a&gt;.\nVerse.\n\"Come to me, Stendarr, for without you, I might be deaf to the manswarm murmurings of thy people, and forgetting their need for comfort and wisdom, I might indulge myself in vain scribbling.\""}
{"id": "173172", "revid": "26709586", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=173172", "title": "Stendarr's Aura", "text": "Stendarr's Aura is an Adept level &lt;a href=\"Restoration%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;Restoration&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Spells%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;spell&lt;/a&gt; in that creates an aura around the caster which &lt;a href=\"Sun%20Damage%20%28Dawnguard%29\"&gt;damages&lt;/a&gt; nearby &lt;a href=\"Undead%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt;.\nLocations.\nIt can only be bought if the &lt;a href=\"Dawnguard%20%28Faction%29\"&gt;Dawnguard&lt;/a&gt; are sided with. &lt;a href=\"Florentius%20Baenius\"&gt;Florentius Baenius&lt;/a&gt; at &lt;a href=\"Fort%20Dawnguard\"&gt;Fort Dawnguard&lt;/a&gt; will sell the tome after he is rescued in \"&lt;a href=\"Bolstering%20the%20Ranks\"&gt;Bolstering the Ranks&lt;/a&gt;.\"\nIt is, however, possible to buy the tome if the &lt;a href=\"Volkihar%20Clan%20%28Dawnguard%29\"&gt;Volkihar Clan&lt;/a&gt; is joined, by using a &lt;a href=\"Calm%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;Calm&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Pacify\"&gt;Pacify&lt;/a&gt; spell on &lt;a href=\"Florentius%20Baenius\"&gt;Florentius Baenius&lt;/a&gt; during the quest \"&lt;a href=\"Destroying%20the%20Dawnguard\"&gt;Destroying the Dawnguard&lt;/a&gt;.\" Once calmed, he can be spoken to and the tome may be bought from him."}
{"id": "56351", "revid": "17401442", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56351", "title": "Stendarr's Beacon", "text": "Stendarr's Beacon is a watchtower in that is located in &lt;a href=\"The%20Rift%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;The Rift&lt;/a&gt;. A few &lt;a href=\"Vigilants%20of%20Stendarr\"&gt;Vigilants of Stendarr&lt;/a&gt; reside here.\nLocation.\nStendarr's Beacon is located south east of &lt;a href=\"Riften%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;Riften&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Broken%20Helm%20Hollow%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;Broken Helm Hollow&lt;/a&gt;, and south of &lt;a href=\"Giant%27s%20Grove\"&gt;Giant's Grove&lt;/a&gt;.\nNorth-east of this fort is also the location of the \"gateway\" to &lt;a href=\"Morrowind\"&gt;Morrowind&lt;/a&gt;, where it is impossible to cross, unless using &lt;a href=\"Console%20Commands%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;console commands&lt;/a&gt;.\nTo the north of the watchtower lies the entrance to the &lt;a href=\"Dayspring%20Canyon\"&gt;Dayspring Canyon&lt;/a&gt; which leads to &lt;a href=\"Fort%20Dawnguard\"&gt;Fort Dawnguard&lt;/a&gt;. The Dragonborn must come down the mountain from the beacon, and look for the small hole in the side of the mountain in front of them. It will be marked by lit torches.\nDescription.\nStendarr's Beacon is a tower home to several Vigilants of Stendarr and effectively one of the final holdouts after the Volkihar vampires decimated them at the &lt;a href=\"Hall%20of%20the%20Vigilant\"&gt;Hall of the Vigilant&lt;/a&gt;. The bottom of the tower contains a shrine to &lt;a href=\"Stendarr\"&gt;Stendarr&lt;/a&gt; and the top holds an unlocked &lt;a href=\"Containers%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;chest&lt;/a&gt;. Stealing from this will cause the Vigilants and Hold guards to attack and/or arrest the Dragonborn if spotted. There is a &lt;a href=\"cooking\"&gt;cooking&lt;/a&gt; spit beside the tower, and to the other side of it is a table laid out with &lt;a href=\"Food%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;food&lt;/a&gt; on top and a satchel."}
