{"id": "848974", "revid": "17401442", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=848974", "title": "Stomping Sinmur", "text": "Stomping Sinmur is a &lt;a href=\"Quests%20%28Online%29\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; available in .\nWalkthrough.\nAfter completing &lt;a href=\"Securing%20the%20Pass\"&gt;Securing the Pass&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Vigrod%20Wraithbane\"&gt;Vigrod Wraithbane&lt;/a&gt; will tell you that it will be difficult to defeat &lt;a href=\"Sinmur\"&gt;Sinmur&lt;/a&gt; without the shards of Wuuthrad. He will suggest looking for them in &lt;a href=\"Lost%20Prospect\"&gt;Lost Prospect&lt;/a&gt;. If you have not looked there already, you can go there to find shards of &lt;a href=\"Wuuthrad%20%28Online%29\"&gt;Wuuthrad&lt;/a&gt;. Alternatively, you can seek the help of your allies to defeat Sinmur. Either way, go through the door to Trolhetta Summit and speak with &lt;a href=\"Jorunn%20the%20Skald-King\"&gt;Jorunn the Skald-King&lt;/a&gt;. He will lead the charge against the final remnants of the Worm Cult. Once you've fought your way through the worm cult, you will find yourself up against Sinmur himself. \nIf you collected the shards of Wuuthrad, \nIf you have not collected any of the shards of Wuuthrad, the fight will be more difficult. Sinmur packs a powerful punch, but after doing some damage, the spirit of &lt;a href=\"Thallik%20Wormfather\"&gt;Thallik Wormfather&lt;/a&gt; will temporarily get separated from him, at which point he is vulnerable. After defeating him, the spirits of &lt;a href=\"Ysgramor%20%28Online%29\"&gt;Ysgramor&lt;/a&gt; and his &lt;a href=\"Five%20Hundred%20Companions\"&gt;Five Hundred Companions&lt;/a&gt; will appear to congratulate you in your victory, and to warn that a hard road still lies ahead. After listeing to them, speak with Jorunn. He will tell you that he is worried about Ysgramor's warning. He will ask you to speak with Vigrod, who is waiting outside. After speaking with Vigrod, speak with Jorunn again to finish the quest and the &lt;a href=\"Ebonheart%20Pact\"&gt;Ebonheart Pact&lt;/a&gt; questline."}
